Working with Dates
Date transformations are among the most common operations in data preparation. Power Query provides dedicated date functions accessible from the Transform tab:
•  Extract: Year, Month, Day, Quarter, Week of Year, Day of Week, Day Name, Month Name.
•  Calculate: Age (difference between dates), Start/End of Month, Start/End of Quarter.
•  Parse: Text to Date conversion with format specification.
These extractions create new columns that enable time-based analysis downstream — grouping by month, filtering by quarter, or building date dimension tables.
Conditional Logic
The “Add Conditional Column” feature (under Add Column) creates if/then/else logic visually:

// Visual conditional column: order_size
// If [amount] >= 1000 Then "Large"
// Else If [amount] >= 100 Then "Medium"
// Else "Small"

// Generated M code:
= Table.AddColumn(#"Previous Step", "order_size", each
    if [amount] >= 1000 then "Large"
    else if [amount] >= 100 then "Medium"
    else "Small",
    type text)

-- Create schemas for organizational clarity
CREATE SCHEMA staging;
CREATE SCHEMA gold;
CREATE SCHEMA audit;

CREATE PROCEDURE gold.usp_refresh_customers
    @load_date DATE = NULL
AS
BEGIN
    -- Default to today if no date provided
    SET @load_date = ISNULL(@load_date, CAST(GETUTCDATE() AS DATE));

-- Analysts can read gold tables but nothing else
GRANT SELECT ON SCHEMA::gold TO [AnalystGroup];
DENY SELECT ON SCHEMA::staging TO [AnalystGroup];
DENY SELECT ON SCHEMA::audit TO [AnalystGroup];

-- ETL service principal can write to staging, read/write gold
GRANT SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE ON SCHEMA::staging TO [ETLServicePrincipal];
GRANT SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE ON SCHEMA::gold TO [ETLServicePrincipal];
GRANT EXECUTE ON SCHEMA::gold TO [ETLServicePrincipal];

-- Grant access to specific columns only
GRANT SELECT ON gold.dim_customers
    (customer_id, customer_name, region, segment)
TO [AnalystGroup];

-- Deny access to sensitive columns
DENY SELECT ON gold.dim_customers (email) TO [AnalystGroup];

